# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Env file hierarchy (Next.js / Node convention)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This file (.env.example)        committed.       Documents required vars. NO SECRETS.
# .env                             gitignored.     Non-secret local defaults.
# .env.local                       gitignored.     **Local secrets go HERE.** Per-machine.
# .env.development.local           gitignored.     Local overrides for `next dev`.
# .env.production.local            gitignored.     Local overrides for `next start` (rare).
#
# Production / preview deployments: secrets are injected by Vercel / AWS Amplify
# at build & runtime — they are NOT read from any .env file in the repo.
#   Vercel:  Project Settings → Environment Variables
#   Amplify: App → Hosting → Environment Variables
# The `amplify.yml` build phase writes scoped vars from the Amplify env scope to
# `apps/web/.env.production` at build time, keyed by this `.env.example` file.
#
# Per-app envs live in apps/*/.env.example. This root file is referenced by
# `turbo.json` globalDependencies so changes bust the build cache appropriately.
#
# Pre-commit hook: secretlint scans every staged file. If you accidentally stage
# a credential (AWS key, GitHub token, Stripe key, etc.), the commit is rejected.
